items.title: 2-D Electronics' metal or semiconductor? Both
items.summary: Researchers produced the first 2-D field-effect transistor (FET) made of a single material.

items.title: How patients are likely to respond to DNA drugs
items.summary: Research could lead to improvements in treating patients with diseases caused by mutations in genes, such as cancer, cystic fibrosis and potentially up to 6,000 other inherited conditions.

items.title: 'King Tide' mapping project
items.summary: 'Dress rehearsal' will help quantify local flooding risk and validate storm-surge models, while laying groundwork for a long-term network of volunteer data collectors.

items.title: When it comes to the threat of extinction, size matters
items.summary: Animals in the Goldilocks zone -- neither too big, nor too small, but just the right size -- face a lower risk of extinction than do those on both ends of the scale, according to an extensive global analysis.
